## 10. Mixed Practice: Fractions, Decimals, Coordinates, and Volume

### Example 49: A Real-World Problem—Splitting a Pizza

<!-- BUILD: Run this program. You have a pizza cut into 8 slices. You eat 3 slices (3/8), your friend eats 2 slices (2/8 = 1/4). How much is left? -->

```scheme
(define total (exact/rat 8 8))
(define you-ate (exact/rat 3 8))
(define friend-ate (exact/rat 2 8))
(define left (exact/- (exact/- total you-ate) friend-ate))
(print \"Total pizza: \" (exact/->string total))
(print \"You ate: \" (exact/->string you-ate))
(print \"Friend ate: \" (exact/->string friend-ate))
(print \"Pizza left: \" (exact/->string left))
```

**Output:**
```
Total pizza: 1/1
You ate: 3/8
Friend ate: 1/4
Pizza left: 3/8
```

[VISUAL: Text output showing the exact fractions. Optionally, a circular pizza diagram divided into 8 slices, with 3 shaded one color (you), 2 shaded another (friend), and 3 left unshaded.]

---

### Example 50: A Decimal Word Problem—Shopping Bill

<!-- BUILD: Run this program. You buy three items: $12.50, $8.75, and $5.99. Compute the total. -->

```scheme
(define item1 12.50)
(define item2 8.75)
(define item3 5.99)
(define total (+ (+ item1 item2) item3))
(print \"Total bill: $\" total)
```

**Output:**
```
Total bill: $27.24
```

[VISUAL: Text output showing the total bill. Optionally, a receipt-style graphic listing the three items and the sum.]

---

