### Example 53: Volume of a Rectangular Prism Using Fraction Dimensions

<!-- BUILD: Run this program. A box has dimensions 7/2 (length), 5/3 (width), and 2 (height). Compute its exact volume. -->

```scheme
(define length (exact/rat 7 2))
(define width (exact/rat 5 3))
(define height (exact/rat 2 1))
(define volume (exact/* (exact/* length width) height))
(print \"Volume (exact): \" (exact/->string volume))
(print \"Volume (decimal): \" (exact/->float volume) \" cubic units\")
