### Example 55: Adding Fractions to Find a Total Distance

<!-- BUILD: Run this program. You walk 3/4 of a mile, then 1/2 a mile. How far did you walk in total? -->

```scheme
(define first-leg (exact/rat 3 4))
(define second-leg (exact/rat 1 2))
(define total-distance (exact/+ first-leg second-leg))
(print \"First leg: \" (exact/->string first-leg) \" miles\")
(print \"Second leg: \" (exact/->string second-leg) \" miles\")
(print \"Total distance: \" (exact/->string total-distance) \" miles\")
```

**Output:**
```
First leg: 3/4 miles
Second leg: 1/2 miles
Total distance: 5/4 miles
```

[VISUAL: Text output showing the exact fractions. Optionally, a number line from 0 to 2, with markers at 3/4, then an arrow to 3/4 + 1/2 = 5/4.]

---

### Example 56: Converting the Distance to a Mixed Number

<!-- BUILD: Run this program. It converts 5/4 miles to a mixed number (1 1/4). -->

```scheme
(define total (exact/rat 5 4))
(define mixed (exact/->mixed total))
(print \"5/4 miles = \"
       (car mixed) \" and \"
       (exact/->string (exact/rat (cadr mixed) (caddr mixed)))
       \" miles\")
```

**Output:**
```
5/4 miles = 1 and 1/4 miles
```

[VISUAL: Text output showing the mixed number.]

