### Example 58: A Volume Problem with Mixed Numbers

<!-- BUILD: Run this program. A crate has dimensions 5 1/2 inches (length), 3 3/4 inches (width), and 2 inches (height). Convert the mixed numbers to improper fractions and compute the exact volume. -->

```scheme
(define length (exact/rat (+ (* 5 2) 1) 2))    ; 5 1/2 = 11/2
(define width (exact/rat (+ (* 3 4) 3) 4))     ; 3 3/4 = 15/4
(define height (exact/rat 2 1))                ; 2
(define volume (exact/* (exact/* length width) height))
(print \"Volume (exact): \" (exact/->string volume) \" cubic inches\")
(print \"Volume (decimal): \" (exact/->float volume) \" cubic inches\")
```

**Output:**
```
Volume (exact): 165/4 cubic inches
Volume (decimal): 41.25 cubic inches
```

[VISUAL: Text output showing both the exact and decimal volume.]

